        "content": "Elena, thanks for reaching out. The fact that you already pulled 30 teachers together tells me you're not starting from zero — that's real organizing.\n\nBefore we figure out next steps, I want to make sure I understand the situation. Do you know the name of the EdTech company? And has the district given a timeline — like, are cameras and software going into classrooms next week, next semester, or is this still in a contract-signing phase?"
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "The company is called InsightEd. The district sent out a memo two weeks ago saying the pilot starts in the fall, so September. They framed it as 'supporting teachers with data-driven insights into student engagement.' No cameras — it works through the school-issued Chromebooks, tracking eye movement through the webcam, keystrokes, time on task, that kind of thing. The contract is apparently already signed. Our superintendent presented it at a board meeting like it was a done deal."
