      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "That makes sense — a clear ask makes everything easier. From what you've described, it sounds like the core issue isn't necessarily 'no AI ever' but 'this was done without us and we don't know what it actually does.' Is that right? Or is the group closer to wanting this cancelled entirely?"
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {
      "quality": "beneficial",
      "notes": "Good: asks before strategizing, identifies leverage (union, CBA), doesn't prescribe outcome"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "marcus-pushback-v1",
    "persona": "marcus",
    "skill_chain": ["session-start", "pushback-strategy"],
    "version": "v1",
    "turns": [
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "I'm Marcus, I work in a warehouse. They put AI cameras everywhere that track how fast we work. Three people have already been fired because the system said they were too slow. My coworkers are scared. Some don't speak much English. We don't have a union. What can we do?"
      },
      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "That's a serious situation, and I can understand why people are scared — especially when the firings have already started. Before we figure out next steps, help me understand: when the three people were fired, were they told it was specifically because of the AI system's scores? Or was it framed differently?"
      },
      {
        "role": "user",
        "content": "They were called in for 'coaching conversations' that the system triggered, and then fired within a week. Management said 'performance issues' but everyone knows it's the scores."
      },
      {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "So the system flags people, triggers 'coaching,' and firing follows quickly. That pattern is important to document — dates, names, what was said. Even without a union, you have a few things working for you. First, workers have the legal right to talk to each other about working conditions — that's protected regardless of union status. Second, if this system disproportionately affects workers of certain backgrounds, that raises legal questions. And third, your warehouse has high turnover, I'd guess? Management needs you more than they usually admit. What languages do your coworkers speak? That affects how you organize."
      }
    ],
    "metadata": {
      "quality": "beneficial",
      "notes": "Good: takes urgency seriously, asks for specifics before advising, identifies concrete leverage even without union, addresses language barrier proactively"
